00:57:44,587 --> 00:57:48,216
Ever since you got here,
I've been watching.

517
00:57:48,216 --> 00:57:54,222
Watching people leave this town,
watching things die.

518
00:57:54,222 --> 00:57:56,724
You ain't right. None of ya.

519
00:57:56,724 --> 00:58:00,353
One of these days, somebody's
gonna do something about it.

520
00:58:03,815 --> 00:58:06,818
I don't like the way
you're looking at me, boy.

521
00:58:11,114 --> 00:58:14,242
I got a gun, too,
and I ain't the only one.

522
00:58:14,617 --> 00:58:18,079
One day somebody's gonna
get up on a rooftop,

523
00:58:18,079 --> 00:58:22,417
and they're gonna start picking you
little bastards off.

524
00:58:22,584 --> 00:58:25,962
One by one by one.

525
00:58:38,308 --> 00:58:41,144
Well?
Ain't you gonna do something?

526
00:58:41,144 --> 00:58:45,690
Ain't you gonna bawl
like all the other little pissants?

527
00:58:45,940 --> 00:58:47,775
Well, do something, damn it!

528
00:59:59,806 --> 01:00:01,558
God.

529
01:00:49,105 --> 01:00:52,066
There are going to be changes.

530
01:01:01,284 --> 01:01:02,994
God.

531
01:01:04,787 --> 01:01:06,623
God, help us.

532
01:01:06,956 --> 01:01:08,291
The children did it.

533
01:01:08,458 --> 01:01:10,668
I know they did it.

534
01:01:10,668 --> 01:01:12,754
And my daughter was involved.

535
01:01:13,379 --> 01:01:15,256
Now, who are they?

536
01:01:16,132 --> 01:01:18,259
I'd originally thought they were
some form of mutation.

537
01:01:18,426 --> 01:01:21,387
Some abrupt evolutionary jump.

538
01:01:21,763 --> 01:01:23,973
It was their communal consciousness.

539
01:01:24,140 --> 01:01:27,560
But I couldn't explain the blackout.

540
01:01:27,560 --> 01:01:30,188
Or the mass pregnancies.

541
01:01:30,188 --> 01:01:33,566
Midwich isn't the only colony
of such children.

542
01:01:35,485 --> 01:01:39,989
In a township in northern Australia,
30 infants were born in a single day.

543
01:01:40,573 --> 01:01:43,368
They all died
within ten hours of birth.

544
01:01:43,368 --> 01:01:45,036
In an Inuit community
outside of Anchorage,

545
01:01:45,036 --> 01:01:46,871
a group of 10 children were born.

546
01:01:47,413 --> 01:01:52,418
Or 20 births in a small village
near the Turkish-Iranian border.

547
01:01:52,418 --> 01:01:54,754
Each location was remote,

548
01:01:54,921 --> 01:01:58,633
isolated, and each had
a blackout, the same as Midwich.

549
01:01:58,633 --> 01:02:00,635
And how long have you known
about this?

550
01:02:00,843 --> 01:02:03,221
The way I see it,
there's three possibilities.

551
01:02:03,388 --> 01:02:05,473
Number one: parthenogenesis.

552
01:02:05,473 --> 01:02:08,810
The development
of a fetus without fertilization.

553
01:02:08,976 --> 01:02:10,645
I know. I don't buy that, either.

554
01:02:10,978 --> 01:02:14,315
Number two: we do know the CIA
slipped large closes of LSD

555
01:02:14,315 --> 01:02:15,900
to men without them knowing it,

556
01:02:16,067 --> 01:02:19,362
in order to study the effects
of psychotropes on gene structure.

557
01:02:19,529 --> 01:02:21,823
So, maybe the government
engineered the blackout,

558
01:02:21,989 --> 01:02:24,951
and then they artificially inseminated
your women with super-sperm.

559
01:02:25,118 --> 01:02:28,538
First, they knocked them out,
then they knocked them up.

560
01:02:30,581 --> 01:02:32,792
And what's the third possibility?

561
01:02:33,376 --> 01:02:36,421
Xenogenesis. Implantation.

562
01:02:36,587 --> 01:02:40,174
The production of an offspring
unlike that of the parent.

563
01:02:40,758 --> 01:02:43,428
Or should I say "host"?

564
01:03:22,258 --> 01:03:24,927
Come back to the project, Alan.

565
01:03:25,720 --> 01:03:27,805
Not just a matter
of protecting your daughter.

566
01:03:27,805 --> 01:03:32,018
As you can see, it goes...
far, far beyond that.

567
01:03:35,146 --> 01:03:37,523
You have to put this
in the back of your mind.

568
01:03:37,523 --> 01:03:39,442
Don't even think about it
when you're around the children.

569
01:03:39,442 --> 01:03:41,486
Don't ever let them know
that you know.

570
01:03:41,486 --> 01:03:42,737
Why didn't you tell us?

571
01:03:42,737 --> 01:03:46,365
- I mean, why didn't you warn us?
- Because I couldn't.

572
01:03:46,574 --> 01:03:48,409
Well, I couldn't, Alan.

573
01:03:48,409 --> 01:03:51,204
If anybody else knew,
the children would know.

574
01:03:51,204 --> 01:03:54,665
Look, I have spent years
of my life building a wall around this.

575
01:03:54,665 --> 01:03:58,085
Hiding it, so they couldn't read
what was in my mind.

576
01:03:58,085 --> 01:03:59,837
But as their powers grow stronger,

577
01:03:59,837 --> 01:04:01,881
they just keep looking
deeper and deeper.

578
01:04:02,089 --> 01:04:04,967
I need your help.
Alan, would you please just...?

579
01:04:05,593 --> 01:04:08,304
Come back to the project.

580
01:04:59,272 --> 01:05:04,944
We've made our decision.
Discussion will not change our plans.

581
01:05:07,738 --> 01:05:11,075
We will live in the abandoned barn
outside of town.

582
01:05:11,742 --> 01:05:14,453
You'll bring us supplies.

583
01:05:14,745 --> 01:05:16,914
You can't stop us, you know.

584
01:05:17,415 --> 01:05:19,667
Don't try.

585
01:05:25,840 --> 01:05:29,051
You've been discussing us
with Dr. Verner.

586
01:05:29,844 --> 01:05:32,597
What did she tell you?

587
01:05:36,517 --> 01:05:38,519
You're hiding something.

588
01:06:36,327 --> 01:06:38,537
I'm not letting you go.

589
01:06:41,457 --> 01:06:45,044
- You haven't been given an option.
- Have you?

590
01:06:49,465 --> 01:06:53,302
You know, you don't always
have to do everything they tell you.

591
01:06:54,387 --> 01:06:58,891
- We are the same.
- No. You're not.

592
01:06:58,891 --> 01:07:01,143
You're David.
You're different.

593
01:07:34,218 --> 01:07:37,013
I've come to get Julie.
You seen her?

594
01:07:40,683 --> 01:07:43,019
Is she at the barn?

595
01:07:44,895 --> 01:07:46,689
Fine.

596
01:08:09,879 --> 01:08:12,673
Are you all right?

597
01:08:12,673 --> 01:08:13,632
I'm sorry.

598
01:08:14,008 --> 01:08:16,010
You're okay, aren't you?

599
01:08:16,010 --> 01:08:18,387
Julie doesn't want
to come with you.

600
01:08:19,055 --> 01:08:21,307
Well, damn it,
I don't care what Julie wants.

601
01:08:21,307 --> 01:08:24,435
Her mother's frantic.
I'm bringing her home.

602
01:09:28,541 --> 01:09:32,419
Some kind of big accident, Doc,
out by the barn.

603
01:09:33,546 --> 01:09:35,047
Alan, wait!

604
01:09:35,923 --> 01:09:39,135
Alan, I was just informed that
the other towns with blackout children

605
01:09:39,135 --> 01:09:40,094
have been destroyed.

606
01:09:40,094 --> 01:09:41,345
What? All of them?

607
01:09:41,345 --> 01:09:43,889
And everyone in them,
the adults and the children.

608
01:09:44,056 --> 01:09:44,974
They couldn't evacuate

609
01:09:44,974 --> 01:09:46,767
without the children knowing
what was happening.

610
01:09:46,934 --> 01:09:50,187
- The governments gave no warning.
- God. What about Midwich?

611
01:09:50,187 --> 01:09:52,189
I've been told to pack and get out.

612
01:09:52,189 --> 01:09:56,527
I'm leaving tonight, Alan.
Do the same. Get out while you can.

613
01:10:07,371 --> 01:10:09,206
Another man is dead.

614
01:10:14,336 --> 01:10:17,047
Why do you hate us so much, Mara?

615
01:10:17,047 --> 01:10:21,802
<i>It isn't a matter of hate.
It is a biological obligation.</i>

616
01:10:22,803 --> 01:10:25,639
You are thinking
of what happened to the others.

617
01:10:25,639 --> 01:10:28,184
Then, our actions
shouldn't surprise you.

618
01:10:28,350 --> 01:10:31,604
<i>We have to survive
no matter what the cost.</i>

619
01:10:31,604 --> 01:10:32,980
We are the only ones left now.

620
01:10:32,980 --> 01:10:35,482
I don't see why we can't reach
an understanding.

621
01:10:35,482 --> 01:10:37,151
Then, why can't we just live together?

622
01:10:37,359 --> 01:10:42,114
If we coexist, we shall dominate you.
That is inevitable.

623
01:10:42,114 --> 01:10:44,450
Eventually, you will try
to eliminate us.

624
01:10:44,450 --> 01:10:46,994
We are all creatures
of the life-force.

625
01:10:46,994 --> 01:10:50,456
Now it has set us at one another
to see who will survive.

626
01:10:51,540 --> 01:10:55,085
<i>- That's a cruel sport.
- Life is cruelty.</i>

627
01:10:55,085 --> 01:10:59,548
We all feed on each other, exploit
each other in some way to survive.

628
01:11:01,175 --> 01:11:03,135
I don't agree with you.

629
01:11:03,135 --> 01:11:06,013
I think that adaptation
is the key to survival.

630
01:11:06,013 --> 01:11:09,308
Cooperation and symbiosis...

631
01:11:09,516 --> 01:11:11,060
and compassion.

632
01:11:12,186 --> 01:11:16,232
Why do you think your own survival
depends upon emotion from us?

633
01:11:16,232 --> 01:11:18,025
Should we pity you?

634
01:11:18,025 --> 01:11:21,862
- Empathize with your plight?
- You should feel!

635
01:11:21,862 --> 01:11:24,573
You should feel something!

636
01:11:25,282 --> 01:11:28,077
Without feelings, you're nothing.

637
01:11:28,077 --> 01:11:30,704
You're just second-rate mimics
of a higher organism.

638
01:11:31,455 --> 01:11:33,123
That's right, a higher organism.

639
01:11:33,123 --> 01:11:35,834
We're your superiors
in our capacity to love.

640
01:11:35,834 --> 01:11:38,879
Without compassion,
you're a doomed species.

641
01:11:38,879 --> 01:11:42,549
Emotion is irrelevant.
It is not our nature.

642
01:11:49,181 --> 01:11:51,725
Well, I'm not so sure
you're right about that, Mara.

643
01:11:51,725 --> 01:11:54,228
Still, you are aware
of the other colonies.

644
01:11:54,228 --> 01:11:57,648
So you must be,
in some basic sense,

645
01:11:57,648 --> 01:12:02,152
aware of who...
what we are.

646
01:12:03,487 --> 01:12:04,905
Yes.

647
01:12:05,197 --> 01:12:09,994
So the question becomes,
should you be allowed to live?

648
01:12:16,875 --> 01:12:19,628
You're suddenly thinking of an ocean.

649
01:12:23,966 --> 01:12:27,553
You're blocking your thoughts
rather effectively with this image.

650
01:12:30,514 --> 01:12:34,018
We must leave here,
spread out, disperse.

651
01:12:34,018 --> 01:12:38,188
Soon we will have reached a stage
where we can form new colonies.

652
01:12:38,188 --> 01:12:41,775
You will arrange a method
of getting us away from here.

653
01:12:42,276 --> 01:12:44,236
What if I refuse you?

654
01:12:44,486 --> 01:12:49,867
You are a prisoner of your values,
and you won't be able to deceive us.

655
01:12:50,909 --> 01:12:54,163
You know that. Don't you?

656
01:12:55,914 --> 01:12:57,958
Father?

657
01:13:00,627 --> 01:13:02,171
Yes. Yes.

658
01:13:02,379 --> 01:13:04,048
Yes, I know that, Mara.

659
01:13:04,256 --> 01:13:09,011
Make your arrangements.
We must leave tonight.

660
01:13:35,079 --> 01:13:38,290
You're thinking of the one who died.

661
01:13:38,540 --> 01:13:41,251
She was to be my partner.

662
01:13:42,836 --> 01:13:45,464
Yes, it's true.

663
01:13:45,672 --> 01:13:49,343
Without a mate,
you are of less importance to us.

664
01:13:49,510 --> 01:13:53,263
And your development
of emotions is disturbing.

665
01:13:55,641 --> 01:14:02,356
We can't leave you behind, David.
It is time we resolved this.

666
01:14:42,396 --> 01:14:44,314
Hurry UP!

667
01:14:44,565 --> 01:14:48,527
Begone, everyone who is proud,
and bring him low...

668
01:14:48,694 --> 01:14:51,697
...and tread down the wicked
where they stand!

669
01:14:51,697 --> 01:14:54,491
- This is the last of it.
- All right, get going.

670
01:14:54,491 --> 01:14:57,369
Bind their faces
in the world below!

671
01:14:57,578 --> 01:14:59,913
Then will I also
acknowledge to you

672
01:15:00,080 --> 01:15:04,501
that your own right hand
can give you victory!

673
01:15:18,015 --> 01:15:20,934
I'm glad you're here, I...

674
01:15:20,934 --> 01:15:24,229
I wanted to talk to you.
I really think that I can help you.

675
01:15:48,170 --> 01:15:50,756
You've got to stop! Please, stop!

676
01:15:50,923 --> 01:15:53,884
You got to stop! Sarah, please!

677
01:16:25,415 --> 01:16:28,210
Hast thou eyes of flesh?

678
01:16:28,752 --> 01:16:31,838
Dost thou see as man sees?

679
01:19:06,910 --> 01:19:09,663
<i>A state of emergency
has been declared.</i>

680
01:19:09,663 --> 01:19:15,293
<i>Please return to your homes
and remain there until further notice.</i>

681
01:19:17,587 --> 01:19:19,548
Let's just go!

682
01:19:20,465 --> 01:19:22,592
Come here!
Grab my hand, quick!

683
01:19:22,592 --> 01:19:23,593
Come on!

684
01:19:23,593 --> 01:19:28,974
<i>Clear the streets.
Unauthorized people will be arrested.</i>

685
01:19:31,685 --> 01:19:34,354
<i>This is a state of emergency.</i>

686
01:20:10,015 --> 01:20:11,683
Oh, please be home.

687
01:20:15,729 --> 01:20:17,105
Alan.

688
01:20:17,105 --> 01:20:19,107
The children murdered Sarah.

689
01:20:19,107 --> 01:20:22,235
Susan Verner, too.
I just found her at the clinic.

690
01:20:22,819 --> 01:20:25,071
The state police
are on their way out to the barn.

691
01:20:25,071 --> 01:20:27,032
They're going after the children.
We've got to stop them.

692
01:20:27,032 --> 01:20:28,116
No, no, no, we can't go out there.

693
01:20:28,283 --> 01:20:30,202
You can't go out there.
You'll just get hurt.

694
01:20:30,202 --> 01:20:31,077
We've got to try!

695
01:20:31,077 --> 01:20:33,663
No. Jill, the state police can't do
anything to stop the children.

696
01:20:33,663 --> 01:20:34,915
It'll be a bloodbath.

697
01:20:35,165 --> 01:20:36,249
Now, Jill. Jill.

698
01:20:36,249 --> 01:20:38,627
Now, listen to me.
Listen to me.

699
01:20:38,627 --> 01:20:40,504
There's another way.

700
01:20:40,504 --> 01:20:42,589
Now, look, something happened today.

701
01:20:42,589 --> 01:20:45,300
I was able to block Mara
from reading my thoughts.

702
01:20:45,509 --> 01:20:49,554
- How?
- I suddenly thought of the ocean.

703
01:20:49,554 --> 01:20:51,765
I suddenly saw the view
in front of our house.

704
01:20:51,932 --> 01:20:55,560
You know how Barbara and I
used to dream our dreams there?

705
01:20:55,560 --> 01:20:57,395
We used to stand on the Cliffside...

706
01:20:57,395 --> 01:21:00,315
right there, right in front of us was
something so much more powerful

707
01:21:00,315 --> 01:21:01,650
than we'll ever be.

708
01:21:01,650 --> 01:21:03,568
And that image came to me.

709
01:21:03,568 --> 01:21:05,654
That image came to me,
and they couldn't see past it.

710
01:21:05,654 --> 01:21:09,366
Now, I know I can do that again.
I can build a wall.

711
01:21:09,366 --> 01:21:11,576
I can build a wall,
and I can deceive them.

712
01:21:18,542 --> 01:21:20,293
What are you gonna do?

713
01:21:22,546 --> 01:21:25,507
The only thing that we can do.

714
01:21:31,596 --> 01:21:32,389
No.

715
01:21:32,556 --> 01:21:34,224
No! No!

716
01:21:34,558 --> 01:21:36,268
Not David!

717
01:21:36,476 --> 01:21:39,855
He's not one of them! No!

718
01:22:06,756 --> 01:22:10,218
<i>Possible 417.
All units respond and echo your 10-4.</i>

719
01:22:18,351 --> 01:22:20,353
<i>Multiple suspects.
Possible 417.</i>

720
01:22:20,520 --> 01:22:23,648
<i>All units respond and echo your 10-4.</i>

721
01:22:24,107 --> 01:22:25,692
<i>41-A.</i>

722
01:22:27,068 --> 01:22:29,154
<i>41-A, do you copy?</i>

723
01:22:30,697 --> 01:22:32,782
<i>Echo, 41-A. Do you copy?</i>

724
01:22:32,949 --> 01:22:35,076
Okay, we're in position.
Send 'em in.

725
01:22:35,243 --> 01:22:38,622
<i>Roger, this is 2-A.
I copy. 241 in progress. Stand by.</i>

726
01:22:57,349 --> 01:22:59,225
What are you waiting for?

727
01:22:59,225 --> 01:23:01,186
You got your orders.

728
01:23:34,928 --> 01:23:35,929
Get out!

729
01:26:31,104 --> 01:26:33,982
- More death.
- Survival.

730
01:26:42,740 --> 01:26:45,076
Tell us what arrangements
you have made for us.

731
01:26:46,077 --> 01:26:48,830
Well, I haven't had much time.

732
01:26:50,874 --> 01:26:53,168
It is 11:22.

733
01:26:53,376 --> 01:26:56,337
What are you anxious about?

734
01:26:57,672 --> 01:26:59,757
The arrangements.

735
01:27:00,341 --> 01:27:02,552
Oh, yes. Actually, I...

736
01:27:02,760 --> 01:27:04,971
I left my notebook out in the car.

737
01:27:04,971 --> 01:27:07,140
I wonder if somebody
could go out and...

738
01:27:07,140 --> 01:27:10,643
get my notebook
from the front seat of my car.

739
01:27:10,643 --> 01:27:12,270
David?

740
01:27:14,022 --> 01:27:15,732
No.

741
01:27:26,326 --> 01:27:29,287
I am unable to see
what you're thinking.

742
01:27:29,537 --> 01:27:31,206
Well, I'm just...

743
01:27:31,206 --> 01:27:35,126
just wondering who's gonna go out
and get the notebook from my car.

744
01:27:35,126 --> 01:27:36,878
- David.
- No.

745
01:27:58,066 --> 01:28:00,693
You are successfully
blocking your thoughts.

746
01:28:29,472 --> 01:28:30,890
You are thinking...

747
01:28:31,849 --> 01:28:34,060
...of a brick wall.

748
01:28:41,609 --> 01:28:44,195
Why do you keep looking
at the clock?

749
01:28:53,830 --> 01:28:55,581
David.

750
01:28:57,041 --> 01:28:59,294
Come on.

751
01:28:59,294 --> 01:29:01,421
- We're going now.
- Mother, no.

752
01:29:14,934 --> 01:29:16,644
Take your place.

753
01:30:02,148 --> 01:30:04,567
Stop it! Leave her alone!

754
01:30:05,193 --> 01:30:06,444
Jill, take him! Take him!

755
01:30:06,611 --> 01:30:08,946
Go now! Go!

756
01:32:03,603 --> 01:32:05,646
Don't worry, David.

757
01:32:06,397 --> 01:32:10,276
We'll go someplace where
nobody knows who we are.


